  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement stage: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering stage: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration stage: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy\n\nLegal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Intentionally disguising the source of criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Transferring or converting property knowing it represents criminal proceeds\n- Concealing or disguising the true nature, source, location, ownership, or control of funds\n\nSpecific legal requirements and penalties differ between countries.",
